g.text: Every Repository has injected speciﬁc data
source client. In repository you ask data
source with a speciﬁc payload. Deﬁne separate
repository for separate data source. Use Unit
Of Work pattern in case of dependency.
Data source is represented by deﬁnition of it's
client. Every data source should have it's own
client implementation which is injected then
to repository. Data source deﬁne it's own data
Data source client returns data in it's own
speciﬁc format ( Data Model ). As repository
has an access to domain structures, it should
map Data Models to Domain models in a scope
which are abstractions for data sources.
Eventually you can inject here also Unit of
Work. Ask repository for data through
Domain Structures like Use Case, Scenario,
Presentation layer or triggers some business
In data store you can keep data for a speciﬁc
framework. Data store deﬁnition may vary
depending on used framework ( Redux etc )
In this ﬂow Data Store is treated as separate
data source and is accessed same way as
Presenter exposes speciﬁc set of functions which
has a clear deﬁnition of input ( Request Object )
through which asks for data required by upper
Presenter returns Presentation model to UI
structures which then can be mapped ( if needed )
Product feature has injected presenter which
can ask for data which is required to display
data for user or for markup related logic.
UI Layer may deﬁne it's own models if you need, but in
general you should use presentation models. In some of the
cases you may try to use domain models but it's better to
keep them separated. UI Layer asks through presenter with
use of request object for data to display it for user with use
